Ireland: Murroe Primrose Cottage, a four-bedroom detached house extending to 154sq m (2,100sq ft) lies within easy reach of the University of Limerick, Castletroy College and the village of Murroe. Set on a site of almost half an acre, the cottage originally dates from 1930 but was completely renovated in 2017. Interiors are lovely with an all-white palette, and exposed stone walls add interest. Price: €335,000 Agent: rooneys.eu Portugal: Lisbon With views of the river Tagus, this brand new development at Prata Riverside Village is said to take its influence from the work of architect Renzo Piano. This one-bedroom unit measuring 47sq m (505sq ft) has private parking and a sunny terrace. Communal facilities include a riverside cycle path, leisure areas and terraces. Price: €330,000 Agent: sothebysrealty.com Italy: Tuscany Dating from 1650 and totally renovated in 2010, this 60sq m (646sq ft) one-bedroom apartment is set over four floors and comes with its own olive store, which is 20km away. Interiors are simply beautiful, full of rustic charm with views to the town of Montpulciano. There is a small garden with the property, which is located in the small village of Castelmuzio, 8km from the papal city of Pienza. Price: 3.2 million Norwegian Kr/€321,269 Agent: finn.no France: Mauvezin With views to the Pyrenees, this incredible former presbytery dates back to the 15th century. With a cave in the basement and an all-important turret, interiors have superb features such as parquet flooring, huge fireplaces and exposed walls and beams. The property, renovated in 2013, has five bedrooms and a garden which has room for a pool. Price: €335,000 Agent: frenchproperty.com Cyprus: Paphos This three-bedroom detached villa is located close to the famous Coral Bay beach, and just a few minutes’ drive to Paphos. The gardens have a pool and are swathed in colourful bougainvillea. The property, constructed in 2005, has income potential as a short-term rental unit due to its popular location. Price: €330,000 Agent: sothebysrealty.com